
Overview of adv hopelessly

The adv hopelessly has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                      
1. (3) hopelessly -- (in a hopeless manner; "the papers were hopelessly jumbled"; "he is hopelessly romantic")
2. dispiritedly, hopelessly -- (in a dispirited manner without hope; "the first Mozartian opera to be subjected to this curious treatment ran dispiritedly for five performances")
3. hopelessly -- (without hope; desperate because there seems no possibility of comfort or success; "he hung his head hopelessly"; "`I must die,' he said hopelessly")
